old 486 and dual ide controller

     I'm trying to get an old 486 board, 30 pin simms, vlb, working with
     two hard drives and a cd-rom. No matter what I do I can't get two
     ide ports working. I've tried different controllers, disabling the
     secondary controller on the vlb, and putting a dedicated ide
     controller on. No luck. Nothing is working. Is there a limitation on
     some old motherboards in respect to ide controllers so that the
     board will not support dual ide?
     Any help most appreciated.
     ------------------
     All's well that breaks well.
     [This message has been edited by krafty (edited 12-08-98).]
